response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Counting Divisors\", \"description\": \"Write a function `count_divisors` that counts the number of divisors for a given integer. A divisor is an integer that divides another integer evenly without leaving a remainder.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer for which to count the number of divisors.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns an integer representing the number of divisors for the input integer.\\n\", \"code\": \"def count_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n    count = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            count += 1\\n    return count\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_divisors(4) == 3\", \"assert count_divisors(7) == 2\", \"assert count_divisors(12) == 6\"] }"
